    "extras": [
      "Best weather is usually June–September; outside this window Song-Kul camps close quickly and high passes can turn muddy or snowy.",
      "Shared taxis and marshrutkas leave when full, so keep the plan flexible and start rural transfer days early.",
      "Carry cash for bazaars, yurt camps, horse riding and village cafés; card acceptance is reliable in Bishkek but patchy at the lakes and almost absent at Song-Kul.",
      "Even in July and August, Song-Kul nights can feel near-freezing, so pack thermals and a windproof layer.",
      "A Bishkek–Osh domestic flight is the cleanest way to cover the north-south split without losing a full extra road day.",
      "If you only have one week, keep Bishkek, Karakol, Issyk-Kul and Song-Kul and save Osh for a separate south-Kyrgyzstan trip."
    ],
